{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@","kind":"attribute"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSTextInput","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"mentions","mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Controls"]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Layout","text":"Layout"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Text input is based on several configurable UI elements:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"label"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": It is used to describe the purpose of the input."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In some UI contexts, especially when space is limited or when the input is part of a compact layout (search bars, filters, inline forms), the label can be hidden."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However, hiding the label should only be done if the purpose of the input remains clear thanks to a placeholder or contextual icon"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and if the label is still accessible to screen readers"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Hiding a label is a design choice that must balance visual simplicity and clarity of intent, without compromising inclusiveness or form guidance."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"placeholder"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": if the text of the text input is empty a placeholder provides a hint or guidance inside the field to suggest expected input."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A prefix and a suffix can be added to give more context."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"leading icon"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": it helps indicate the purpose of the input (magnifying glass for search, envelope for email, phone device for phone number)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Only use a leading icon if it adds clear functional or contextual value."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"trailing action","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": it is used to provide actions related to the field: clear input, toggle password visibility, open a date picker, etc."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Can also indicate status or feedback (error checkmark, loading spinner)."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Outlined-style","text":"Outlined style"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default"}]},{"type":"text","text":", the input is with a subtle background fill and invisible bottom border, creating a softer and more contained look."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Best suited for dense layouts or to enhance visibility."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"outlined"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":", the text input is a minimalist design with a transparent background and a visible stroke outlining the field."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This style may be interesting for contexts other than form pages:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When inputs need to feel lightweight and unobtrusive","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In a header (search field)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In a selection\/filtering feature in a product catalog"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"code":["   \/\/ An outlined text input","   OUDSTextInput(label: \"Label\", text: $text, isOutlined: true)","","   \/\/ With a localizable and a bundle","   OUDSTextInput(LocalizedStringKey(\"label_wording\"), bundle: Bundle.module, text: $text)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Rounded-layout","level":3,"text":"Rounded layout","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Text input can have rounded layouts to be favored in more emotional, immersive contexts or those tied to specific visual identities.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"For standard or business-oriented journeys, keep the default corners.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This evolution addresses the need for flexibility in adapting the design to some brand contexts."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To activate the rounded corner behavior, set to true the ","type":"text"},{"code":"hasRoundedTextInputs","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" values of the "},{"code":"Tuning","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" object"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in your theme configuration (if the theme exposes this property at init)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Some themes do not have this flexibility like ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SoshTheme"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"WireframeTheme"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Status","anchor":"Status","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Five status are proposed for all layouts:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default (by default)"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Default neutral appearance, whether empty or filled."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It allows users to click, focus, and type freely without restrictions."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"error"}]},{"type":"text","text":": The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"error"},{"type":"text","text":" status indicates that the user input does not meet validation rules or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"expected formatting. It provides immediate visual feedback, typically through a red border,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"error icon, and a clear, accessible error message positioned below the input. The error messages replaces the helper text."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"loading"}]},{"type":"text","text":": The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"loading"},{"type":"text","text":" state indicates that the system is processing or retrieving data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"related to the text entered. A progress indicator appears to inform the user that an action is in progress."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"readOnly"}]},{"text":" :The","type":"text"},{"code":"readOnly","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", lets the text visible but not editable"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"disabled","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": In "},{"code":"disabled","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" status, the field is non-interactive and grayed out to indicate it cannot be changed."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Note the SwiftUI "},{"code":"View.disabled()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is ignored."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Helpers","text":"Helpers","type":"heading","level":2},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Helper text","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":":  A supporting text conveys additional information about the input field,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"such as how it will be used. It should ideally only take up a single line, though may wrap","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to multiple lines if required, and be either persistently visible or visible only on focus."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Helper link","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": If the helper text is not sufficient, it’s possible to offer the user"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"an additional help link (the link can be external or open a modal).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Accessibility-considerations","level":2,"text":"Accessibility considerations","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default no haptics are done by the component for the trailing action."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However you should think about cases wher you will have to make the devices vibrates."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"You can refer to the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/design\/human-interface-guidelines\/playing-haptics","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Mandatory field indication","anchor":"Mandatory-field-indication","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If all fields are mandatory (several fields present): display the message “All fields are mandatory” at the top of your formular.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Do not use an asterisk at the end of each field label, nor the word “mandatory.”","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If not all fields are mandatory (several fields present): display the message “All fields marked with an * are mandatory” at the top of your formular.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Use an asterisk (*) at the end of each mandatory field label, and ensures this is well vocalized.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"UI rendering of the asterisk must be done with ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"bold font weight","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"negative content color","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" (red on light backgrounds).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use the mention “(optional)” at the end of each optional field label. Note that this rule is not systematic, it remains an option, to be used if needed.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If there is only one field in the formular, or if the mandatory nature is obvious (such as login\/password),","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"no mention is necessary since the fields are essential to the formular’s functionality.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Code-samples","text":"Code samples","level":2},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ The text to display and edit","    @State var text: String = \"\"","","    \/\/ Empty text and no placeholder","    OUDSTextInput(label: \"Email\", text: $text)","","    \/\/ Empty text with placeholder and suffix","    OUDSTextInput(label: \"Email\", text: $text, placeholder: \"firstName.lastName\", suffix: \"@orange.com\")","","    \/\/ Empty text with prefix and suffix","    OUDSTextInput(label: \"Email\", text: $text, prefix: \"Distance\", suffix: \"km\")","","    \/\/ Add a leading icon for more context","    OUDSTextInput(label: \"Email\", text: $text, placeholder: \"firstName.lastName\", suffix: \"@orange.com\", leadingIcon: Image(systemName: \"envelope\"))","","    \/\/ Add a trailing button with local image namde \"ic_cross\" for additional action","    let trailingAction = OUDSTextInput.TrailingAction(icon: Image(\"ic_cross\"), actionHint: \"Delete\") { text = \"\" }","    OUDSTextInput(label: \"Email\", text: $text, trailingAction: trailingAction)","","    \/\/ With helper text","    OUDSTextInput(label: \"Email\",","                  text: $text,","                  placeholder: \"firstName.lastName\",","                  suffix: \"@orange.com\",","                  helperText: \"The email will be automatically completed with @orange.com\")","","    \/\/ With helper link","    @Environment(\\.openURL) private var openUrl","","    let helperLink = OUDSTextInput.HelperLink(text: \"Helper Link\") {","       openUrl.callAsFunction(url)","    }","","    OUDSTextInput(label: \"Label\", text: $text, placeholder: \"Placeholder\", helperLink: helperLink)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you need to flip your icon depending to the layout direction or not (e.g. if RTL mode lose semantics  \/ meanings):","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    @Environment(\\.layoutDirection) var layoutDirection","","    OUDSTextInput(label: \"Label\", text: $text, flipLeadingIcon: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft)"]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Design-documentation","text":"Design documentation"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-text-input"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Themes-rendering","text":"Themes rendering"},{"level":3,"text":"Orange","anchor":"Orange","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_textInput_Orange"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Orange-Compact","text":"Orange Compact"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_textInput_OrangeCompact"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Sosh","text":"Sosh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_textInput_Sosh","type":"image"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Wireframe","text":"Wireframe"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_textInput_Wireframe"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Version","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"1.3.0 (Figma component design version)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0.20.0"}]}],"style":"note","name":"Since","type":"aside"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTextInput","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Text input is a UI element that allows to enter, edit, or select single-line textual data."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Text input is one of the most fundamental form elements used to capture user input such as names, emails, passwords, or search queries."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It provides a visual and interactive affordance for text entry while supporting labels, placeholders, icons, descriptions, and validation feedback."}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTextInput\/Helperlink","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTextInput\/TrailingAction"],"title":"Structures","generated":true,"anchor":"Structures"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTextInput\/init(_:tableName:bundle:text:placeholder:prefix:suffix:leadingIcon:flipLeadingIcon:trailingAction:helperText:helperLink:isOutlined:constrainedMaxWidth:status:)","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTextInput\/init(label:text:placeholder:prefix:suffix:leadingIcon:flipLeadingIcon:trailingAction:helperText:helperLink:isOutlined:con